00:35:36,669 --> 00:35:39,859
Are you saying he is really the culprit?

324
00:35:39,859 --> 00:35:44,309
Goodness! He's smart, his family is wealthy, and he has so much going for him.

325
00:35:44,309 --> 00:35:48,919
Why would someone who lacks nothing commit something so horrendous? Geez...

326
00:35:48,919 --> 00:35:51,239
So if you're not smart and don't have much, it's okay to do that?

327
00:35:51,239 --> 00:35:54,359
- No, no, that's not what we meant. 
 - Soon Ae's dad, that's not what we're saying.

328
00:35:54,359 --> 00:35:57,739
I raised my precious daughter with devotion, too.

329
00:35:57,739 --> 00:35:59,819
So tired of all the gossiping.

330
00:35:59,819 --> 00:36:02,269
 Geez, come on now.

331
00:36:02,869 --> 00:36:04,329
 Geez...

332
00:36:11,009 --> 00:36:16,719
 After a month-long search, the suspect of the Woojeong Village serial murder case has finally been arrested.

333
00:36:16,719 --> 00:36:21,369
 The nightmare of the nervous townspeople finally ended.

334
00:36:21,369 --> 00:36:23,879
 Reporter Kim relays the events.

335
00:36:23,879 --> 00:36:27,549
 Yoon, the suspect behind the month-long serial murder cases in Woojeong Village

336
00:36:27,549 --> 00:36:31,039
 has been apprehended and is now entering the police station.

337
00:36:31,039 --> 00:36:35,089
 Surrounded by swarming cameras, Yoon was transported to the police interrogation room.

338
00:36:35,089 --> 00:36:38,299
 The suspect, Yoon, denied the murder charges, but

339
00:36:38,299 --> 00:36:41,639
 the police confirmed that they have the evidence that proves

340
00:36:41,639 --> 00:36:46,539
 the handwriting on the note found at the crime scene matches Yoon's handwriting.

341
00:36:49,629 --> 00:36:52,449
Now it really feels like everything is over.

342
00:36:53,249 --> 00:36:57,559
We caught the culprit, and I think I did everything I could here.

343
00:36:58,719 --> 00:37:02,839
The car is fixed, too, and now...

344
00:37:03,539 --> 00:37:06,069
we should take time to return.

345
00:37:07,239 --> 00:37:09,189
You mean, we should leave?

346
00:37:09,189 --> 00:37:12,329
We can't continue living like nonexistent people.

347
00:37:13,019 --> 00:37:15,699
We also have to check the changed future.

348
00:37:20,129 --> 00:37:25,389
You need some time to say goodbye to your mom, dad, and other family members.

349
00:37:27,869 --> 00:37:30,890
So how about we leave tomorrow night?

350
00:37:36,779 --> 00:37:38,939
All right.

351
00:37:38,939 --> 00:37:40,869
Let's do that.

352
00:38:01,889 --> 00:38:03,849
Do you want that?

353
00:38:08,106 --> 00:38:10,976
I told you I don't want to see anyone!

354
00:38:11,679 --> 00:38:15,279
Is there still no news from my dad?

355
00:38:30,009 --> 00:38:34,389
I'll trust you and leave you alone, so come out after you're done talking.

356
00:38:35,789 --> 00:38:37,299
Yes.

357
00:38:51,839 --> 00:38:54,129
I was wondering who the owner of this good fortune would be.

358
00:38:54,129 --> 00:38:55,859
But it's ultimately you, Hee Seop.

359
00:38:55,859 --> 00:38:59,259
You drooled looking at it every day and said you didn't have any money.

360
00:38:59,259 --> 00:39:01,849
Lucky you! Receiving such a gift from your girlfriend!

361
00:39:01,849 --> 00:39:04,129
- What do you mean, "girlfriend"? 
 - What do you mean, "girlfriend"?

362
00:39:08,619 --> 00:39:10,799
- No, really. 
 - This isn't it.

363
00:39:10,799 --> 00:39:13,369
- I'm not going to buy it! 
 - Stay still!

364
00:39:17,819 --> 00:39:21,329
Are you crazy? Is 200,000 won a joke?

365
00:39:21,329 --> 00:39:23,759
Why would you give this to me?

366
00:39:23,759 --> 00:39:26,529
This probably isn't even your money!

367
00:39:29,229 --> 00:39:32,319
You stole from Mr. Yoon, didn't you?

368
00:39:32,319 --> 00:39:35,089
- If you get caught, then only I'll get in— 
 - Hey!

369
00:39:36,219 --> 00:39:40,379
I'll pay him back later, so just grab it and come out!

370
00:39:40,379 --> 00:39:42,729
So annoying!

371
00:39:50,239 --> 00:39:53,479
Here! It's really yours now!

372
00:40:02,319 --> 00:40:05,989
- Thank you, customer. 
 - Goodness.

373
00:40:05,989 --> 00:40:09,749

374
00:40:13,779 --> 00:40:15,509
Wow!

375
00:40:32,089 --> 00:40:34,079
You don't, by any chance...

376
00:40:35,439 --> 00:40:38,009
like me or anything...

377
00:40:50,359 --> 00:40:52,379
It's a bribe!

378
00:40:58,659 --> 00:41:03,919
Going forward, be good to my best friend Soon Ae for the rest of your life.

379
00:41:03,919 --> 00:41:08,259
If you make Soon Ae tear up even once,

380
00:41:08,259 --> 00:41:11,029
I won't sit still.

381
00:41:11,819 --> 00:41:14,559
Is this a bribe or a threat?

382
00:41:14,559 --> 00:41:18,909
I'll take care of all that myself. Why do you care?

383
00:41:20,059 --> 00:41:22,929
No matter how difficult situations may get,

384
00:41:23,939 --> 00:41:27,279
don't ever break up and stay by each other's side.

385
00:41:29,459 --> 00:41:34,709
Only then... will I be able to see you guys again.

386
00:41:38,229 --> 00:41:40,279
Are you going somewhere?

387
00:41:43,689 --> 00:41:46,479
We'll probably see each other again soon.

388
00:41:49,269 --> 00:41:52,909
Although it might take a little longer for you.

389
00:41:52,909 --> 00:41:55,789
What are you talking about?

390
00:41:55,789 --> 00:41:59,350
By chance, does your head hurt again?

391
00:42:02,199 --> 00:42:04,679
You don't seem to have a fever...

392
00:42:09,919 --> 00:42:11,789
That's enough! Go!

393
00:42:15,270 --> 00:42:16,890

394
00:42:18,499 --> 00:42:22,099
Oh, it feels a little weird.

395
00:42:44,419 --> 00:42:47,649
Dad, lead a good life this time.

396
00:42:49,159 --> 00:42:51,319
Don't get sick.

397
00:42:52,319 --> 00:42:54,659
Without getting hurt...

398
00:42:56,689 --> 00:42:59,609
Do whatever you wish to do.

399
00:43:10,299 --> 00:43:12,979
Why would you kill me?

400
00:43:13,939 --> 00:43:17,119
That's the one thing I really wanted to ask you.

401
00:43:19,739 --> 00:43:22,539
I guess I'll never find out.

402
00:43:23,169 --> 00:43:26,469
Since the future where you could kill me is gone.

403
00:43:36,060 --> 00:43:39,760

404
00:44:41,369 --> 00:44:42,959
How fun.

405
00:45:06,939 --> 00:45:11,439

406
00:45:37,039 --> 00:45:44,199

407
00:45:53,039 --> 00:45:54,939
Was that it?

408
00:45:55,829 --> 00:46:00,219
Because I had killed you, you came to take revenge for that?

409
00:46:01,539 --> 00:46:04,529
If you were that curious, why didn't you just leave it alone?

410
00:46:05,229 --> 00:46:07,529
So that I don't get caught this time, either.

411
00:46:08,369 --> 00:46:13,149
So that I can kill you one more time.

412
00:46:13,149 --> 00:46:20,099
Even though you lived so far away, who knew you would be such a different person?

413
00:46:20,909 --> 00:46:22,519
What?

414
00:46:22,519 --> 00:46:24,849
The conclusive evidence.

415
00:46:25,939 --> 00:46:31,279
After finding the love letters, I became curious about one thing.

416
00:46:36,689 --> 00:46:38,239
 Hae Joon.

417
00:46:38,239 --> 00:46:41,719

418
00:46:41,719 --> 00:46:44,359
You're a smart guy.

419
00:46:44,359 --> 00:46:48,989
You didn't leave behind any mistakes at the crime scenes.

420
00:46:48,989 --> 00:46:51,769
Why did you miss that?

421
00:46:51,769 --> 00:46:55,289
You must have known that the letters could be used as evidence.

422
00:46:55,289 --> 00:47:01,669
You must have known that she could end everything for you with those letters.

423
00:47:03,539 --> 00:47:06,369
Why did you leave her alone?

424
00:47:11,229 --> 00:47:13,579
Did you actually love her?

425
00:47:18,559 --> 00:47:22,379
You're really asking me an unexpected question.

426
00:47:23,079 --> 00:47:29,579
I thought you'd ask me questions like why or how I killed them.

427
00:47:34,059 --> 00:47:35,659
Love?

428
00:47:38,429 --> 00:47:40,049
I did.

429
00:47:40,589 --> 00:47:43,219
I did love her.

430
00:47:43,219 --> 00:47:46,609
I believed she was a woman who could make my dreams come true.

431
00:47:48,729 --> 00:47:51,569
I thought that woman would be different.

432
00:47:52,609 --> 00:47:54,419
Different from the...

433
00:47:55,539 --> 00:47:58,139
terrible woman I knew.

434
00:47:59,889 --> 00:48:05,489
The woman I remember mostly was reading books.

435
00:48:05,489 --> 00:48:13,509
I have no memory of her giving me a warm look. Not even once.

436
00:48:13,509 --> 00:48:17,349
Then one day, when I was seven years old,

437
00:48:18,290 --> 00:48:19,190

438
00:48:19,199 --> 00:48:21,979
she left our home.

439
00:48:21,979 --> 00:48:26,179
Supposedly, she no longer wanted to live as someone's mother.

440
00:48:33,709 --> 00:48:35,589
 Should I...

441
00:48:36,569 --> 00:48:39,279
 meet my mom once?

442
00:48:41,129 --> 00:48:43,299
 Mom?

443
00:48:43,299 --> 00:48:46,589
 You know what your mom is up to?

444
00:49:09,839 --> 00:49:12,939
Being abandoned by the person...

445
00:49:12,939 --> 00:49:18,159
who should love me unconditionally in this world.

446
00:49:18,159 --> 00:49:21,029
Do you know how horrible that feels?

447
00:49:21,029 --> 00:49:24,189
While longing for the person who abandoned me,

448
00:49:24,189 --> 00:49:28,219
I cried and cried all night.

449
00:49:28,219 --> 00:49:33,019
I promised myself during that endless agony.

450
00:49:34,849 --> 00:49:39,839
If I ever have a son someday...

451
00:49:42,839 --> 00:49:44,619
My son.

452
00:49:45,419 --> 00:49:49,539
I will never let my child live the way I did.

453
00:49:49,539 --> 00:49:53,839
I will meet a woman who loves him more than anyone else.

454
00:49:55,059 --> 00:49:57,749
We will live happily ever after.

455
00:49:59,589 --> 00:50:03,759
That's why I met that kind of woman.

456
00:50:04,799 --> 00:50:06,439
She was...

457
00:50:07,379 --> 00:50:09,529
an orphan.

458
00:50:09,529 --> 00:50:13,619
She really wanted to have a family of her own.

459
00:50:15,309 --> 00:50:18,269
Did you know you almost made that happen?

460
00:50:20,269 --> 00:50:23,969
- What? 
 - That family you so longed for.

461
00:50:23,969 --> 00:50:27,899
The perfect happiness. The perfect family.

462
00:50:28,499 --> 00:50:31,809
Do you know you ruined it all by yourself?

463
00:50:31,809 --> 00:50:33,919
What are you saying?

464
00:50:34,759 --> 00:50:37,049
But what a relief.

465
00:50:37,049 --> 00:50:42,779
That my mom could escape a bastard like you.

466
00:50:58,959 --> 00:51:00,669
You...

467
00:51:01,959 --> 00:51:04,479
You're not by any chance...

468
00:51:11,929 --> 00:51:14,179
That's nonsense...

469
00:51:15,800 --> 00:51:21,400
If you're really my son, you couldn't do this to me.

470
00:51:21,400 --> 00:51:23,199
No...

471
00:51:23,199 --> 00:51:25,999
How could I even kill you?

472
00:51:25,999 --> 00:51:29,309
Thanks to having a terrible father like you,

473
00:51:29,309 --> 00:51:33,359
I'll explain it to you as an abandoned child from birth.

474
00:51:33,359 --> 00:51:36,389
All the things you rattled on about up until now...

475
00:51:37,619 --> 00:51:43,679
is nothing but silly self-pity from a killer with a victim mindset.

476
00:51:45,579 --> 00:51:49,909
So for the rest of your life, all the remaining time you have,

477
00:51:49,909 --> 00:51:53,749
stay locked up and rot away in agony.

478
00:51:55,639 --> 00:52:00,609
This is the last wish of the son you desperately longed to have.

479
00:52:53,574 --> 00:52:55,564
Mr. Yoon!

480
00:52:56,524 --> 00:52:57,764
- Oh, goodness. 
 - Yes?

481
00:52:57,764 --> 00:53:00,074
Why are you all out here? Is something wrong?

482
00:53:00,074 --> 00:53:02,204
What do you think?

483
00:53:02,204 --> 00:53:04,914
We heard you're moving! On top of that, tonight!

484
00:53:04,914 --> 00:53:08,284
How could you leave suddenly, without a word in advance?

485
00:53:08,284 --> 00:53:10,984
I'm really disappointed. You know?

486
00:53:10,984 --> 00:53:12,164
Yes.

487
00:53:12,164 --> 00:53:14,154
I'm really sad, Mr. Yoon.

488
00:53:14,154 --> 00:53:17,384
I consider you as family. But how could you...

489
00:53:31,944 --> 00:53:35,384
I'm telling you, we really will see each other again.

490
00:53:35,384 --> 00:53:37,024
When?

491
00:53:37,964 --> 00:53:40,074
Where?

492
00:53:41,994 --> 00:53:44,764
About 34 years later.

493
00:53:44,764 --> 00:53:46,814
In your home.

494
00:53:48,384 --> 00:53:51,014
I really hate you.

495
00:53:52,314 --> 00:53:56,544
Just say we'll never see each other again.

496
00:53:56,544 --> 00:54:00,024
Say, we'll never see each other again!

497
00:54:01,554 --> 00:54:04,524
So that I don't wait for you any longer.

498
00:54:10,654 --> 00:54:13,024
By that time,

499
00:54:14,814 --> 00:54:18,414
we will look a little different.

500
00:54:21,584 --> 00:54:24,724
But I really like that face, too.

501
00:54:27,604 --> 00:54:32,344
I miss... that face so much, too.

502
00:54:37,234 --> 00:54:41,104
I'm so glad that I was able to come here.

503
00:54:42,434 --> 00:54:44,504
Because I...

504
00:54:45,734 --> 00:54:49,254
Because I was able to meet you as you are now,

505
00:54:50,834 --> 00:54:53,804
and find you again...

506
00:54:55,934 --> 00:54:58,674
I'm so glad.

507
00:55:08,824 --> 00:55:10,714
Me, too.

508
00:55:14,044 --> 00:55:15,934
Me, too.

509
00:55:19,594 --> 00:55:24,574
I was so happy... that I had met you.

510
00:55:52,284 --> 00:55:54,334
Thank you.

511
00:55:58,264 --> 00:56:00,834
Thank you very much, Mr. Yoon.

512
00:56:00,834 --> 00:56:05,014
Thank you very much for being our neighbor, Mr. Yoon.

513
00:56:05,014 --> 00:56:06,634
Oh, yes.

514
00:56:08,364 --> 00:56:10,424
Thank you for saying that.

515
00:56:10,424 --> 00:56:12,184
Oh, gosh.

516
00:56:12,184 --> 00:56:16,874
Thank you so much for helping my sisters, Mr. Yoon!

517
00:56:16,874 --> 00:56:18,464
Yes.

518
00:56:18,464 --> 00:56:22,514
Could you just tell us where you're going?

519
00:56:22,514 --> 00:56:26,424
So that we can think, "Oh, he must be there by now..."

520
00:56:26,424 --> 00:56:28,644
Just the place.

521
00:56:29,414 --> 00:56:33,704
Well, it's very far.

522
00:56:34,524 --> 00:56:37,214
Please stay healthy and live a long life.

523
00:56:37,214 --> 00:56:40,674
I'll be sure to come and visit.

524
00:56:58,164 --> 00:57:00,844
We're really leaving now, aren't we?

525
00:57:01,594 --> 00:57:03,534
Yeah, we are.

